1
00:00:22,070 --> 00:00:24,618
A will? What nonsense are you talking about?

2
00:00:25,490 --> 00:00:27,396
Ms. Pimprapha already had it written, sir.

3
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:31,214
And what does the will say?

4
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:33,781
Uh… I’m afraid I can’t disclose that.

5
00:00:33,803 --> 00:00:35,549
Hey! I told you to tell me!

6
00:00:35,607 --> 00:00:38,414
Well… when Pimchat turns 25

7
00:00:38,443 --> 00:00:42,000
she will legally become the president of P.S. Group.

8
00:00:42,029 --> 00:00:43,854
Then where is the will now?

9
00:00:44,830 --> 00:00:46,596
It has been securely kept, sir.

10
00:00:46,647 --> 00:00:49,672
All witnesses have already signed to acknowledge it.

11
00:00:55,207 --> 00:00:57,210
Damn it!

12
00:00:59,210 --> 00:01:01,210
Damn it!

13
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:05,127
I was so close!

14
00:01:15,290 --> 00:01:19,367
Do you think I’d just let it end like this, Pimprapha?

15
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:43,556
P’Chat, let’s go.

16
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:46,560
What is this?

17
00:03:46,603 --> 00:03:49,461
What is this? Have you been working here for a long time
why can’t you even handle something this simple?!

18
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:52,130
I’m sorry, sir.

19
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:00,218
Dad, where are you rushing off to?

20
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:03,738
To work.

21
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:06,460
Have breakfast with us first, Dad.

22
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,665
Look, the maid made some delicious rice porridge.

23
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:33,447
It’s okay, P’Chat.

24
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,425
He’s probably stressed about work.

25
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:42,363
Yeah, I understand.

26
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:45,847
Dad must really be stressed about work.

27
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:49,505
I just want to get closer to him…

28
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,363
in case I won’t have that chance anymore.

29
00:04:55,190 --> 00:05:00,458
Then… how about we cook something for him today?

30
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:05,323
Cook? But I don’t know how to cook.

31
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,156
Oh..P’Chat!

32
00:05:07,185 --> 00:05:09,490
If he gets to taste your cooking,

33
00:05:09,512 --> 00:05:11,490
I’m sure he’ll be really happy.

34
00:05:15,345 --> 00:05:16,458
Then I’ll try.

35
00:05:16,487 --> 00:05:18,909
Okay, I’ll be your helper, P’Chat.

36
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:31,789
Okay, what should we make?

37
00:05:32,341 --> 00:05:35,861
Hmm… fried rice?

38
00:05:35,898 --> 00:05:37,860
Or maybe a fried egg?

39
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:42,741
You…  Don’t you have any other ideas?

40
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:46,610
That’s all I know how to make.

41
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:50,814
What does he like to eat?

42
00:05:54,254 --> 00:05:56,250
Mom liked basil stir-fry,

43
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,058
and I always saw Dad eating it with her.

44
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:02,370
How about we make that?

45
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:05,025
Sure!

46
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:10,996
let check a recipe first.

47
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,250
Wait, you don’t know how to make it?

48
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:16,203
I don’t…

49
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:17,825
I just want to help.

50
00:08:19,607 --> 00:08:20,661
Uncle,

51
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:23,352
have you eaten yet?

52
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,505
Ah, not yet.

53
00:08:25,534 --> 00:08:26,276
Perfect.

54
00:08:26,312 --> 00:08:29,585
Then please come with me for a moment.

55
00:08:29,614 --> 00:08:30,749
I have something to show you.

56
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:32,814
Alright, let’s go, go.

57
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,014
This way,

58
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:42,087
Please have a seat right here.

59
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:43,090
Dad, you’re back?

60
00:08:43,127 --> 00:08:45,476
Today, P’Chat made your favorite basil stir-fry for you.

61
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:50,203
She put a lot of effort into it.

62
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,952
I’ll leave now.

63
00:08:54,596 --> 00:08:56,600
Today I tried making basil stir-fry.

64
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,600
I saw you always liked eating it with Mom.

65
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:00,261
Give it a try, Dad.

66
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:27,789
Eat a lot, okay?

67
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:34,290
You really do love basil stir-fry.

68
00:09:34,661 --> 00:09:36,660
I used to ask you to eat it with me all the time.

69
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:41,745
Of course. We’re lucky that we like the same things.

70
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:46,043
Yeah, Would you like some more?

71
00:09:47,050 --> 00:09:48,487
Eat plenty, okay?

72
00:09:53,069 --> 00:09:54,341
Eat plenty, okay?

73
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:57,200
Is it delicious?

74
00:10:28,410 --> 00:10:29,258
Yes, Mom.

75
00:10:34,070 --> 00:10:35,738
Don’t worry, Mom.

76
00:10:37,498 --> 00:10:39,927
I’ve been indulging that young lady for a long time.

77
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:42,370
No matter what, we’ll end up getting married anyway.

78
00:10:43,830 --> 00:10:46,429
You should start preparing a beautiful outfit.

79
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:49,643
Yes, Mom.
